compartment_id.description: compartment id where to create all resources

defined_tags.description: predefined and scoped to a namespace to tag the resources created using defined tags.

freeform_tags.description: simple key-value pairs to tag the created resources using freeform OCI Free-form tags.

attached_drg_id.description: the ID of DRG attached to the VCN

compartment_id.description: compartment id where to create all resources

create_internet_gateway.description: whether to create the internet gateway in the vcn. If set to true, creates an Internet Gateway.

create_nat_gateway.description: whether to create a nat gateway in the vcn. If set to true, creates a nat gateway.

create_service_gateway.description: whether to create a service gateway. If set to true, creates a service gateway.

defined_tags.description: predefined and scoped to a namespace to tag the resources created using defined tags.

enable_ipv6.description: Whether IPv6 is enabled for the VCN. If enabled, Oracle will assign the VCN a IPv6 /56 CIDR block.

freeform_tags.description: simple key-value pairs to tag the created resources using freeform OCI Free-form tags.

internet_gateway_display_name.description: (Updatable) Name of Internet Gateway. Does not have to be unique.

internet_gateway_route_rules.description: (Updatable) List of routing rules to add to Internet Gateway Route Table

label_prefix.description: a string that will be prepended to all resources

local_peering_gateways.description: Map of Local Peering Gateways to attach to the VCN.

lockdown_default_seclist.description: whether to remove all default security rules from the VCN Default Security List

nat_gateway_display_name.description: (Updatable) Name of NAT Gateway. Does not have to be unique.

nat_gateway_public_ip_id.description: OCID of reserved IP address for NAT gateway. The reserved public IP address needs to be manually created.

nat_gateway_route_rules.description: (Updatable) list of routing rules to add to NAT Gateway Route Table

region.description: the OCI region where resources will be created

service_gateway_display_name.description: (Updatable) Name of Service Gateway. Does not have to be unique.

subnets.description: Private or Public subnets in a VCN

vcn_cidrs.description: The list of IPv4 CIDR blocks the VCN will use.

vcn_dns_label.description: A DNS label for the VCN, used in conjunction with the VNIC's hostname and subnet's DNS label to form a fully qualified domain name (FQDN) for each VNIC within this subnet. DNS resolution of hostnames in the VCN is disabled when null.

vcn_name.description: user-friendly name of to use for the vcn to be appended to the label_prefix
